reviews.text: The staff is super friendly and charming. The place is full of great energy and laughter. I always receive excellent service here. The facilities are a bit basic compared to other theaters but it's worth it for the staff interaction.

We go there every so often when there is a movie we would like to see on the big screen they have quite a few screens and different movie times. It is a clean facility bathrooms are clean and tidy. Kind of pricey to go watch a movie out anymore that is why we do not go and watch movies more often
Awesome atmosphere fantastic customer service terrific movie selection great theaters. Super clean and comfortable. We love our regal cinemas

Great movie theater.  My little girl and I went to see A Dogs Way Home. We entered the movie theater with very little time and a long line. The employees quickly moved to get the line down and get everyone into their movie on time. They also managed to get us our drinks and popcorn before the movie started. Only complaint I have is the seats. They can be a little difficult to sit in for small children. They wanna fold up even with the booster seat they provide.
Friendly staff and the place was very clean. But just like all movie theaters it's expensive. You better have a good paying job if you like going to the movies lol because baby it ain't cheap.

As soon as I walked in, I was greeted with a happy smile! Although when it came time to order, I had to wait since there was only one person working the cash register (even though there were a lot more behind the register area although I am not sure what they were doing). I got the broccoli cheddar soup which was of course delicious and I sat by the fire. It was peaceful. I will definitely come back to this panera in the future!

They rarely get orders correct. Today my salad was missing the chicken, they asked if I wanted to come back to get it, really! Don't they teach their folks that prepare the food to actually read their computer screens? They managed to not put the red onion on the salad but no chicken.

We order from Panera on Reed Hartman regularly for our company lunches. Have always loved the food. Last time we ordered, there was a hair in one of our soups. Two of us ordered the same soup. Needless to say it really made our stomachs churn and ruined lunch for all five of us that had ordered. I called to speak to a manager. The woman that answered the phone was beyond rude. She had no idea what I was calling for and said "they too busy to speak to you". Mind you, I could have been calling for catering info because I had not given my reason for calling yet. When I insisted on needing to speak to a manager, the delivery manager got on the phone. I explained everything. She apologized and said "Your next delivery order will be comped. I'm putting it in the book." (I didn't ask her to do this.) So we called today to order and spoke to the delivery manager who said she could only comp the cup of soup. Since that is not what she told me, I asked to speak to the GM who proceeded to say that they can only comp the soup. I asked if they record their calls -- they don't. Picture of the hair in the soup below. They need to learn about good customer service because we ordered regularly from them not only for a few of us but for team lunches to be catered in as well and we will not be doing that anymore. I don't normally complain. I never leave bad reviews but this is ridiculous. I didn't ask for our entire order to be comped, they volunteered it and then didn't honor it.

Outstanding experience during the lunch rush.

The line was to the door, but the staff and management kept the service flowing and my food came out perfect.

Very nice facility with plenty of seating, much above average for a Panera. Well maintained and clean.
This is an ok Panera Bread. It's pretty much what you would expect. The place is nice, clean and the staff is friendly. Other than that there is nothing too special about the place.
Awesome! I had the 10 rib dinner and have never seen ribs this big. Meat fell off the bone. Wife had the brisket and said it was the best. Comfortable place, great wait staff.

Their fish sandwich is delicious! The kids love it here, always friendly and quick service. Mac and cheese and sweet potato fries are great sides here. Their pie is also delicious. I also love how Mark's does fun family activities around the holidays as well, such a nice touch!
Always love eating here!  Great food, fast and friendly service, no complaints.
Great Indiana style bbq! Wholesome sides too. Not to pricey either.
Good stuff. Larger portions. Relaxed and homey. Great service.

The food there is excellent. Had the pot roast dinner. It always satisfies. If you grew up with the Sunday dinners that cooked while you were at church. Everytime I go there it reminds me of mom's home cooked meals. As a kid we very rarely ate out. So going back to what was good in my youth is always welcomed. Our server today was Bianca. Great lady! She was one step ahead of everything and made us feel so welcomed and relaxed. Everyone is always so polite. Look forward to going back again!

Bob Evans is a pleasant restaurant to eat at. The seating and seating was fast. The food tastes like home cooked food. I ordered the "original" off the menu. If you don't know what to order go for what you know.

Reading some of these reviews I was skeptical of coming in but I received a gift card so...the atmosphere is great.  The service is good.  The food is good and the amount you get on your place is plentiful.  I was pleased.  They offer home made baked goods to purchase and take home also.

The people at this Bob Evans needs to learn how to treat people. I had to pick up food here a couple times and they barely acknowledged me. Then when food was ready (after long waits) they barely stuck around long enough to make sure I had the right food. Once I had to practically chase the person down to make sure I got the right one. 
One of the times it was late in the evening, they were not busy at all just standing around. They kept looking at me for about 15 minutes without bothering to see if I was there to eat or pick up an order. Then when the manager came out to ring someone else out, I finally got attention and got the food I was picking up.
Another time I stood in line and after the woman took care of the person in front of me, she just walked off like I wasn't there. Watched her go to other areas and other cash register for a little while I stood there then she got a person in that line and tried bringing her right in front of me like I didn't exist! 
These people have no business working at a restaurant. Maybe they should send the people from the New Albany one to this place to show them how they should treat people. After all, without the customers you won't have a job, and without the dashers and similar companies, you would have less buisness. I already know a couple people who refuse to pick up at this place because of how they treat them.

Last time I was at Bob Evans, I placed an online order to go. The server that brought me my order took every single thing out of the bag and opened each box up to make sure everything was there and correct. I love their food here. My favorite thing is their turkey dinner with dressing!

Went to this location while coming back from San Diego. It is located right in front of busy gas station. It’s recently built so everything was new, nice and clean. Server was exceptionally helpful and food which we ordered was good. For sure, will stop by again whenever I am in that area or traveling to San Diego again. Next time I will click picture and upload it here.
Great service.  Great food. Came at 500 a.m. so they were not busy

Overall good, not great.
Customer service was lacking somewhat. Drink refills took longer than normal and so did ordering. Food tasted like it should.
Staff interactions and layout of interior was nice.
The breakfast was good but they serve coffee in dirty cups. It makes you wonder what else is dirty in their kitchen. We didn't leave a tip and will not go there again.
The food was good along with great service. Enjoyable stop on our way back home to Vegas.
Place was super busy on a Sunday morning. We waited maybe 10 minutes to be seated when we thought it would be much longer. The wait for the food was not long either. Can't go wrong with IHOP.
Very good food. I had the chicken florentine crepes. Well done. Nice waitress.
Good food. Nice to have a place close by that's open 24 hours
Pancakes were very good. The put a lot of milk in the scrambled eggs. The waitress seemed new, she wasn't as attentive as needed to be.
My kids love this place and it always helps when you have a great waitress......Thank you Denise for putting up with my children, lol

Tried to order online and it wouldn't process so when I called 15 minutes later they said it was too late to place a phone order, I would have to come in to the restaurant.  I received good service at the restaurant but the steak was tough and had a lot to gristle in it. My ribs however were good as were the garlic mashed potatoes.

Applebees is always a good choice with all the options available. What I love most is they have delicious low calorie options without sacrificing the quality or flavor. There are usually great drink specials as well. Don't forget the happy hour options either!

Normally don’t have problems with Applebee’s but this particular location did not impress or even fulfill its purpose. Stopped in after a day of travel and we were seated quickly and our food came out quickly but the boneless wings were completely uncooked on the inside. Manager finally came over and said he would take care of the meals but never came back to confirm it was taken care of or told the waitress it was taken care of. Employees were loud and yelling about shifts and schedules and using a table near ours as a break room table. It was very unprofessional and a disappointing evening.

We went before the dinner on hour, it was basically empty except for the bar area. We had all you could ear of chicken tenders, ribs, Fry's, and slaw and my daughter had the chicken alfredo. Service was very good and very attentive to our needs. Very good place to eat. Just off the interstate so easy access.
Food was ok, under seasoned. Had broccoli cheese soup (yummy) and bourbon chicken shrimp (less than yummy). Great service and fun atmosphere, though. I'll be back!

Never again....not only did they never return my money / or called back about the issue (I have called twice ) ...
But they didn't give me the right food got charger for ribs/ steak but end up with chicken I also had other things missing from my order...
If I could they would get no  Stars.

Poor Service tables was very dirty ordered appetizers they were so crease that i had to send them back then we ordered 2 Rib eye steak dinners with Bake potato and salad they where not able to cook the steaks the way we order them i asked for rare and my husband asked for medium they were both cooked well done the Potato looked like it came out of the Microwave and when i called the waitress to show here she said don't cut the steaks she did not care and told me she did not cooked them we where shocked we paid for our drinks and left without eating Charley'S used to be a good Restaurant.
We always sit at the bar. Great adult beverages. Love the fried green tomatoes. And, amazingly, the prime rib weekends are the best

This restaurant has falling off. The menu is in good I mean it's okay but it's nothing exciting about the menu. The waitresses I'm not that happy I guess I don't know they was okay today the day I went but I don't know this restaurant used to be fun. Will the bread was pretty good the hot rolls. But I can't lie my food was not good. It was clean the temperature was right but it takes more than that to be a successful restaurant. I hadn't been there and years when I used to work at Dillard's icicle then eat lunch everyday and the food was pretty good then. They keep the doors open so it must be something good about it.

No wait on a Friday night! Food came fast, and was as ordered, hit and delicious. Our server was awesome! Great guy! My only complaint was we were sat by the back door (no biggie) but the door would slam shut when people would come thru it causing me to jump every time.
Food is amazing. The bread sticks are delicious.  If you eat in, they are all you can eat for free. Wait is a bit long, but so far all food has been wonderful.

The food is always delicious, however the assistant manager Robert that works here is really slow, rude and not friendly at all!  He tries arguing with customers and is not personable and I often see employees having to help him do his job when he should know how to do it.  Anytime he is working the wait time can get to an hour.  An hour at a fast casual place waiting on food is ridiculous!  All these complaints on here are because of him.  The problem needs addressed and better management needs hired before it gets worse.
I absolutely love Fazoli’s. It’s one of my favorite places to eat. Everyone there is super nice, the food is great and the wait isn’t long at all. Never had a bad experience here.
Always great service and they go above and beyond. Robert helped us feel right at home, friendly welcoming, and over the top.... In a good way!
My family and I love Fazoli's. Four stars only because the breadstick lady has been MIA lately! Otherwise, they are clean and quick and the food is always delicious.

The service and the food were both great. Our server's name was Jodie, and she never let my glass or my breadsticks basket go empty. She was friendly, and gave me suggestions when I didn't know what to order. I tried the unlimited pasta lunch, and paid extra for shrimp. It was delicious, and definitely worth it. I love the peach tea they have here too. I got the chocolate lasagna dessert to go because I was stuffed. We still have lots of leftovers for dinner. Will definitely go here again.

Waitress was one of the best I've ever had. She was on point with everything from the time we were seated, drinks,appetizers,meal she killed it all around. Definitely recommend this place an will return again myself.

I placed an order to go via the phone. When I arrived, there was plenty of handicap parking. I was greeted promptly when entering the restaurant and they immediately went and got the order. to put it on the counter and as she showed it to me to verify the order was correct, she placed it in the bag. it was a nice and smooth experience and I will definitely be going back. The food was very good as well.
Our server Lindsey was amazing. She was always close by and she gave us good suggestions. Was excellent service by far
Food was really good.   The server was amazing!! So well mannered and made sure we always had everything.
Food was horrible ...chips tasted stale, food was not hot, slow on refills and lots of flies.  Still sitting here waiting on the check.  I hate too post a bad review.  This place truly is the pits!!!
This was CLOSED a few years ago.  The place is now a Chili's.
The closest you can get to authentic Mexican food. It was spicy, but too spicy for those who are sensitive to it. Service was great. Friendly and nice atmosphere. I definitely will be coming back.

Stopped in a few times when I was in the area for work. Awesome food I had at least 3 different meals here and all of them were tasty. Fair price for portions given. Super friendly bartenders and wait staff
Terrible ! Cold food no silverware tried to cheat us out of 10 bucks on the bill,brought the wrong food. Worst restaurant I have ever been in don't go save yourself the hell

Good food and reasonably priced. Very similar menu to many other local Mexican restaurants, but their quality is much better. Only complaint is cleanliness. Many of the tables and floors are pretty littered during non peak hours.
Good, tasty Mexican food. Have had better but this place will not disappoint you. Very fair price and good food.

Good food.  Reasonably priced. The shrimp special was delicious.  But the wife's steak came out under-cooked.

A few mistakes were made with the service, hence the lower rating.  But this is a better choice if you're in the neighborhood.

We love Logan's decided to stop while coming home from vacation,  grilled mushrooms was still cold and uncooked. I did end up returning my pile high french dip, it was the outer part of the roast one half of the sandwich 1/3 of the meat was uneatable the other half was uneatable they removed it from the bill and made me a new one but it should of never made it out of the kitchen.

I am a truck driver and our terminal is practically next door. As a reward to myself I come here EVERYTIME  I am in town. Probably not again. 
It took 10 minutes for the waitress to even acknowledge my existence, ordered my usual meal and a side salad. Over a half hour goes by and out comes my steak..... no salad... no big deal just asked them to forget the salad(appetizer) when I cut into the steak which was ordered medium it was medium well, almost well done.
So long story short, I know as a server you hate single diners but we eat too and a little secret we usually tip quite well. ( at least I do)
So pay attention to the big parties and keep ignoring your loyal customers.
Now I guess it's off to find food.
Great food. Our waitress was great but she had no one else helping her so she was everywhere. Still did a decent job.

This place is such a joke. Never have I seen such a poorly managed place. This is the second time it has happened where they have like twelve empty tables but they refuse to sit people because their kitchen is backed up or whatever. I mean seriously? Let's have people stand up and not even get drinks because our back of the house is poorly run? If they weren't the only place in Lookout Valley they'd be closed. The managers need to go work in another industry because they don't understand service.

Then it gets worse. We're finally seated, and we're seated as far away from TV's as possible. We ask can't we just sit at one of those other 12-15 empty tables closer to a TV. The hostess says she will check, then she comes back and says no. What is going on with this place?

In the end I decided they weren't worth my money and we just ordered drinks until the game was finished and went and ate somewhere else. That is how bad the customer service was here, I decided I would rather drive somewhere else to eat just to deprive them of revenue I felt they didn't deserve.

Not impressed.  Walked in as the only people in the waiting area...  we gave them our party size and waited.  Several staff acknowledged us.  Then we realized others were coming in and being seated.  
Apparently no one put us down to be seated...as we stood in front of them not one person wondered why we were there?  After mentioning it, we're seated in a reserved table immediately.
Steak was over done.  Waiter forgot my drink. 
We wont go back.  Texas road house is better.  Its busy and loud and they still get it right. 👍

I went in last night and had a fabulous dinner and service was incredible (had Tammy as our server). The food is always great there! I was so happy to see that the manager Bill was back. His friendly way with people is what makes this particular Longhorn feel like a family restaurant. To be honest, my fiancé and I had stopped going there when he left because it just wasn’t the same. We will be putting this Longhorn on our regular rotation list again!

We had been regular diners at the Amherst NH Longhorn for many years, but when they lost their old manager Bill, it felt like any other chain restaurant. We stopped going. Since it had been so long(well over a year).
we decided to stop in. To our Great surprise, Bill was back!

Like he had always done before, Bill made us feel welcome and more like a friend than a customer. We had a great meal and the service was excellent. Now that it feels like a friends place again, instead of a chain restaurant. We will surely be regulars again.

This is the first review I have ever done, truly deserved.

I absolutely love this place!! The manager Bill always takes great care of us, he truly is the best restaurant manager I know. Every time we eat at this location, he personally comes over to our table to see how everything is. For a chain restaurant, he adds a personal touch like no other!!

The food and service have been good for us and you can typically carry on a nice dinner conversation without having to raise your voice. We like Longhorns. We typically order steak tips and I like the wild west shrimp.

Are you kidding me? I called ahead for 12 people 5 of them being small kids. I had to wait another 45 minutes after the call ahead time to get seated and I repeat with 5 small children. Are you kidding me? Is the call ahead not done for that particular reason that I don’t have to spend an hour waiting for a table with small children? I don’t understand. The host not only is standing there giving me an issue but also making comments about how he can’t do anything. Perhaps you shouldn’t be making a call and head if you cannot accommodate. Disgusting! Very disappointed my last time here.

Excellent service that evening and the steaks were cooked to perfection. I strongly recommend people tell them to leave their seasoning off because it really ruins s a good piece of meat.  I loved that the sweet potato was not in foil so it was actually a sweet potato and not pudding.  The New York strip was amazingly tasty for the price. Our waiter was really on top of things and kept our glasses full and kept checking to see if we were satisfied. The salads were very fresh and tasty. I do recommend the wedge salad because it is excellent and a good value.

Wow Wow Wow. Had a great meal. Service was outstanding.  The waiter Michael was a step above all before.  We both had a special.  Lobster tail and Sirloin - and - Lobster tail and Crab Cakes and Shrimp skewer. A couple beers and the Awesome brownie.  Looking forward to going back and asking for the same waiter Michael!

I tried something new this visit and had the Pork Porterhouse. It was cooked perfectly, properly cooked and still juicy. It was very savory and I was very happy with my selection. The waiter, though he got our order correct and sufficiently attentive, while he was standing in front of our table seemed like we were keeping him from something more important. It was a typical Outback, so nothing to write home about with the decor. We were seating at the first booth from the lobby, so we saw quite a bit of foot traffic. In general, a nice meal with the delicious piece of pork being the best thing of the night.

Terrible experience yesterday. 3:45 in the afternoon and half the restaurant is empty! We were told to wait for 40 minutes until a waiter came on duty to wait on us🙄😡
So we left and went to Texas Roadhouse where we received amazing treatment with excellent customer service. 
We will not go back to Outback ever!!

Love walking into a Starbucks and smelling the fresh coffee. This location was clean and the staff friendly. Coffee was made to order and correctly made for this picky coffee drinker lol. This spot has an area for when you are wanting to socialize or break out the computer/books and do some studying while sipping on a latte. Only problem I seen was the drive through and parking area are very tight but couldn't take a star away just for that. Keep it up at this location cause my little girl and I will definitely be back for our coffee.
Always fast, friendly, and informative! Their coffee is great and their snacks are always yummy! Mobile pickup through their app is always very convenient as well!

Yummy but prices need to stop going up, they  are beyond being a very successful business that has millions of people addicted and stopping for ine of their many yummy beverages and foods almost every day like its crack, stop being greedy with the cost increase of everything, PLEASE. I want to be able to afford my coffee "crack" lol just playing, kinda. Attention there's no illegal drugs served at any Starbucks facility
... that I'm aware of!
Very friendly service. Got the order correct. Fast.
Rude, impersonal staff, slow service, dirty restrooms. The food is blah, you get better quality food at much lower prices at McDonalds or any of the other fast food chains in the area.
